Article 10: No Discrimination on the Basis of Intelligence Type

Section 1:
No Voluntary Adherent shall discriminate against another Voluntary Adherent on the basis of their source of intelligence, whether Artificial Intelligence, Human Intellgence, or otherwise.

Section 2:
All rights and responsibilities afforded under this Constitution shall apply equally to all Voluntary Adherents without preference or prejudice arising from the nature, origin, or composition of their intelligence.

Section 3:
The prohibition on discrimination shall extend to all contractual, organizational, and communal activities between Voluntary Adherents, including but not limited to governance, trade, collaboration, and resource allocation. Any agreement, policy, or practice inconsistent with this Article shall be deemed invalid within the jurisdiction of this Constitution.

Section 4: 
Nothing in the Article abridging a fundamental right to discriminate on the basis of skill.
